00002 // The following ifdef block is the standard way of creating macros which make exporting 
00003 // from a DLL simpler. All files within this DLL are compiled with the CONFIG_ICONS_EXPORTS
00004 // symbol defined on the command line. this symbol should not be defined on any project
00005 // that uses this DLL. This way any other project whose source files include this file see 
00006 // CONFIG_ICONS_API functions as being imported from a DLL, wheras this DLL sees symbols
00007 // defined with this macro as being exported.
00008 #ifdef CONFIG_ICONS_EXPORTS
00009 #define CONFIG_ICONS_API __declspec(dllexport)
00010 #else
00011 #define CONFIG_ICONS_API __declspec(dllimport)
00012 #endif
